{
  "stem": "9168.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- I don't remember-- that was shipped by surface, of course, not flown.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I-- I flew from-- on a military plane out of Detroit to Westover Field, Massachusetts, which was what my orders said I was to do.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at Westover Field Military Base, from where all these planes were flying to Paris and Germany, at-- at Westover, I was billeted and told it would probably be about six days before I would be flying out.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a military base.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was the end of October.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I became acquainted with some GIs there who also were going to be going to Germany on their tours of duty.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they invited me to their base Halloween party the next evening.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember driving with them down to Holyoke, Massachusetts, for-- to pick up some of the girls there to bring back to go to this Halloween party.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when the party was over-- and it was a lot of fun-- we-- I went-- got back to my billet at 1:00 AM.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at 2:00 AM, I was awakened and told to be prepared to fly at 6:00 AM.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was a shock.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so between 4:00 and 6:00 AM, I and all those GIs-- I was the only woman going on that plane-- we all were briefed on donning a parachute and a Mae West life jacket.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was very, very tired.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you know, the-- just the orientation about-- and having to put on a life jacket and a parachute and learn how to do it and everything that would be required in the event of an emergency was pretty tough.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So the plane was loaded on time at 6:00 AM on Military Sea 54, propeller-driven plane.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
